rComments: She ripped off UC Santa Cruz. It was hands down the greatest piece of performance art ever!

This class was useless, the lectures were dragged on as she spoke in her dull voice about 'digital media' as she struggled to use her computer. Easy A, at the least. Completely pointless that attendance lecture was required. RARELY was there something I found interesting, sections were interesting because they were hands on, but brief and easy.

Very horrible professor. Ironic how a digital media professor who claims to create her art on a computer has no idea how to use one during lecture. Discussions are fun, though. A wasteful class, all in all.

HORRIBLE professor. The subject could be interesting, if she knew her way around a computer. a LOT of dead time in class, and not a whole lot covered. I would have dropped the class if it wasn't for the sections - they saved the class, because they are where I did my learning. This professor should not be teaching though. Lecture = waste of time.

Terrible teacher.  The class is called issues in digital media...the issue is that our prof. can't use a computer.  Lecture attendence is mandatory and painful.  She's a nice enough person but shouldn't be teaching.  Ever.  Ever.
